Harm Reduction Coalition Webinar Series
Outreach & Engagement Strategies for Harm Reduction Programs
October 6, 2020
11:00am - 1:00pm, EDT
This workshop will explore provider skills for effective participant engagement in outreach-based service models. Participants will examine the role of self-disclosure during outreach encounters and identify ‘best practices’ to ensure safety for both outreach workers and participants, including de-escalation strategies.
Additionally, this training identifies how harm reduction can more effectively meet diverse client needs by providing appropriate referrals, building alliances, and accessing community resources.

post_text:
Never Use Alone Hotline
1-800-484-3731
(Back up line: 931-304-9452)
www.neverusealone.com
No Judgement, No Shaming, No Preaching, Just Love
If you have no choice but to use alone, call the Never Use Alone hotline. You will be asked your first name, exact location, county, and the number you are calling from. An operator will then stay on the line with you while you use. If you do not respond after a set amount of time after you've used, the operator will notify emergency services of an unresponsive person at your location.

What are "Crank Bugs" or "Meth Mites?"
Meth can make users feel like bugs are crawling on or under their skin. Users pick at their skin to remove the "bugs" causing open sores, which often become infected.

MONITOR - SECURE - DISPOSE
Following these simple steps can help reduce prescription drug abuse.
Monitor - keep track of all medications in your home and monitor all pills and refills
Secure - Keep all medications in a secure location such as a locked cabinet, safe, or private bathroom
Dispose - Properly dispose of all expired or unused medications in your home.
#Prevention #PreventRxAbuse

DO YOU KNOW WHAT SHATTER IS?
A brittle form of BHO (Butane Hash Oil). It has the look of transparent amber glass and has a reputation for being the purest and cleanest type of extract.
text:
DO YOU KNOW WHAT SHATTER IS?
A brittle form of BHO (Butane Hash Oil). It has the look of transparent amber glass and has a reputation for being the purest and cleanest type of extract.

post_text:
DO YOU KNOW WHAT WAX IS?
A common name for marijuana concentrates. It is a softer, opaque oil that has lost its transparency through the extraction process. Depending on the method used to extract it, waxes may take on varying consistencies. Waxes tend to be harder, non-transparent oils. Budder and honeycomb are considered versions of wax.
text:

post_text:
DO YOU KNOW WHAT BUDDER/HONEY/HONEY OIL IS?
Slang terms used to describe marijuana extracts using butane. It is waxy in appearance, like honey or butter. These would be terms to watch for in your child's texts, chats, emails, notebooks, etc.
text:
DO YOU KNOW WHAT BUDDER/HONEY/HONEY OIL IS?
Slang terms used to describe marijuana extracts using butane. It is waxy in appearance, like honey or butter. These would be terms to watch for in your child's texts, chats, emails, notebooks, etc.

post_text:
DO YOU KNOW WHAT BUTANE HASH OIL IS (BHO)?
A highly potent concentrate of cannabinoids made by dissolving marijuana in plant form in a solvent (usually butane). The resulting product is also referred to as budder, honey oil, dabs, or shatter, depending on how it is manufactured. BHO has a very high THC potency. The use of butane in extraction of BHO is cause for safety concern, as it is highly flammable and has resulted in violent explosions.
text:
DO YOU KNOW WHAT BUTANE HASH OIL IS (BHO)?

The resulting product is also referred to as budder, honey oil, dabs, or shatter, depending on how it is manufactured. BHO has a very high THC potency. The use of butane in extraction of BHO is cause for safety concern, as it is highly flammable and has resulted in violent explosions.

post_text:
DO YOU KNOW WHAT AN OIL RIG IS?
A device or bong specially used for smoking marijuana concentrates. Adapters can be added to traditional bongs or pipes. This kind of language would be something to watch for in your child's texts, chats, notebooks, emails, etc.
text:

WHAT IS DABBING?
The practice of smoking the THC-rich extracts of the marijuana plant, in the form of oils, waxes, or shatter, all of which contain extremely large amounts of THC. The extracts are usually prepared with butane (lighter fluid).

post_text:
DO YOU KNOW ABOUT 420?
A way to identify with the marijuana culture. The date, 4/20 is known as a date to celebrate getting high, and the time 4:20, is noted as an “official” time to get high. 420 is found around pop culture, in movies, online, and on shirts and hats. Watch for this language in your child's texts, chats, notebooks, emails, and on your child's clothing.

"Molly" is the powder or crystal form of MDMA, the chemical used in Ecstasy. This drug has been popular at music festivals and is growing in popularity with youth. Watch for Molly references in your child's texts, chats, emails, notebooks, calendars, etc. Click the link below to learn more.

Things you can do as parents/guardians:
Refuse to supply alcohol to anyone under 21
Be at home when your teen has a party
Make sure alcohol is not brought into your home or property
Talk to other parents about not providing alcohol to minors
Create alcohol-free activities in your home for teens
Report underage drinking to local law enforcement
